  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS] After June segregation, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I realized that my assignment to the furrier is not going to be good enough next time such a thing will happen, and therefore, I had to change my assignment.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I have to backtrack here because a few months before that, I was called by the Jewish police to arrive in their headquarters and was told that my younger brother is outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he was brought back from the Russian part of-- of occupied Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the person who smuggled him through wants to be paid off, or he will simply tell the Germans that he is a Jew, and he will be done.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I had-- he wanted 600 zloty at that time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And since I still had the pass to go out of the ghetto, I could go out and see him, but I could not bring him in because he had no identifications.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I had my father's gold watch, which was one of the treasures which we have still kept.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I had to sell it up on the black market to get the 600 zloty-- well, I got more than that-- and go out again and pay to the man the 600 zloty and had to come back to ghetto and go to the office which assigned jobs and-- and issued identification cards, which-- where I had some friends, because this was almost impossible to get at that point.",
      "word_count": 69
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I was fortunate that my friends came through, and they made me a set of identification card and an assignment to-- for my brother to work on the Krakow airport.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And this how I managed to bring my brother back into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
